1) Treasury would prepare by Tuesday evening (October 9) a
                                        contingency plan for US
                                        action in the event of an oil cut-off;

3) CIA and JCS will prepare by noon
                                        Monday (October 8) a judgment of the military situation,
                                        particularly what we can expect in the next day or two;

4) Secretary Kissinger
                                        will check with the President on provision [less than 1 line not
                                        declassified];
